retrofit_techniques.explanation: A maximum of four (4) sentences describing retrofitting techniques applied to the specimen.

1.title: Out-of-Plane Strengthening of Masonry-Infilled RC Frames with Textile-Reinforced Mortar Jackets
1.authors: Lampros N. Koutas, Dionysios A. Bournas
1.glb_failure_mode: Arching action with step-cracking in mortar joints, gradual load drop
1.lcl_crack_pattern: Step-cracking mainly following mortar joints from center toward corners on back face
1.lcl_failure_mechanism: Wall separation from RC frame perimeter, arching action degradation
1.lcl_damage_progression: First cracks at 10kN in central bed joint, propagation toward corners, wall detachment from frame
1.lcl_strain_distribution: Tension strains concentrated at mortar joints, compression at loading points
1.retrofit_techniques: No retrofitting applied - this is the control specimen serving as reference for comparison with TRM-strengthened specimens.

2.title: In-Plane Strengthening of Masonry Infills using TRM Technique
2.authors: Farhad Akhoundi, Graça Vasconcelos, Paulo Lourenço
2.glb_failure_mode: Diagonal cracking of masonry infill with frame-infill separation and brick crushing
2.lcl_crack_pattern: Stair-stepped diagonal cracks along unit-mortar interfaces, separation at frame-infill interface, horizontal sliding cracks
2.lcl_failure_mechanism: Diagonal strut mechanism with progressive separation from RC frame and crushing of brick units adjacent to frame interface
2.lcl_damage_progression: Early frame-infill separation, followed by diagonal cracking, then crushing of bricks near frame interface with plastic hinge formation in RC columns
2.lcl_strain_distribution: High shear strains along diagonal strut path, concentration of compressive strains at loaded corners with tension at opposite corners
2.retrofit_techniques: No retrofit techniques were applied to specimen SIF-I-A as it represents the control unstrengthened specimen tested until collapse to serve as baseline for comparison with TRM-strengthened specimens.
2.comments:
1. The beam and base beam reinforcement need manual edit before usage as there are 2 cross-sections (refer to manuscript for details).
2. The external leaf geometry and properties are defined. User need manually define the internal leaf geometry and properties

3.title: Experimental Evaluation of RC Structures with Brick Infills for 2 Vertical Forest Adaptation in Seismic regions
